pageContext.patina: Dark green patina, mostly rubbed away.
pageContext.associations: Hoard comprising of 2 fragments of socketed axe, 5 winged celts, looped, and 2 fragments of axes. 3 spear-heads, 1 point, 4 pieces of sword blades, 2 mounts, 2 gouges, 2 pieces of bracelets, 1 coiled ring, 1 lump of metal, 21 other small fragments. 12 pieces of pottery from pot in which the hoard was buried.
pageContext.publications: Bulletin Societe Polymathique Morbihan,(Marsille, "inventaire des Depots de Bronze au Morbihan."),Not Marsille's 1913 paper.
pageContext.collection: Formerly M. de la Granciere,Sold at Sotheby's, 22nd July 1930,Lot 21,No. 70[1]
